PolicyAction.name: PolicyAction
PolicyAction.description: A selection between three fundamental actions of a policy: blocking the offending packets, detecting them but allowing them through, or rate-limiting them.

PolicyComponent.name: PolicyComponent
PolicyComponent.description: A selection from among the components of a policy, corresponding to which log file is used to track the associated information.

SslInspectedFlag.name: SslInspectedFlag
SslInspectedFlag.description: A flag indicating if an action was taken on an inspected SSL data stream.

tptPolicyNotifyDeviceID.name: tptPolicyNotifyDeviceID
tptPolicyNotifyDeviceID.description: The unique identifier of the device sending this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyPolicyID.name: tptPolicyNotifyPolicyID
tptPolicyNotifyPolicyID.description: The unique identifier of the policy causing this notification.

tptPolicyNotifySignatureID.name: tptPolicyNotifySignatureID
tptPolicyNotifySignatureID.description: The unique identifier of the signature matching the incoming data stream.

tptPolicyNotifySegmentName.name: tptPolicyNotifySegmentName
tptPolicyNotifySegmentName.description: A string of the format <slot>:<index> that uniquely identifies the segment pertaining to this notification.

tptPolicyNotifySrcNetAddr.name: tptPolicyNotifySrcNetAddr
tptPolicyNotifySrcNetAddr.description: The network address of the source of the packet(s) triggering the policy action.

tptPolicyNotifySrcNetAddrV6.name: tptPolicyNotifySrcNetAddrV6
tptPolicyNotifySrcNetAddrV6.description: The IPv6 network address of the source of the packet(s) triggering the policy action.

tptPolicyNotifySrcNetPort.name: tptPolicyNotifySrcNetPort
tptPolicyNotifySrcNetPort.description: The network port (if applicable) of the source of the packet(s) triggering the policy action.

tptPolicyNotifyDestNetAddr.name: tptPolicyNotifyDestNetAddr
tptPolicyNotifyDestNetAddr.description: The network address of the destination of the packet(s) triggering the policy action.

tptPolicyNotifyDestNetAddrV6.name: tptPolicyNotifyDestNetAddrV6
tptPolicyNotifyDestNetAddrV6.description: The IPv6 network address of the destination of the packet(s) triggering the policy action.

tptPolicyNotifyDestNetPort.name: tptPolicyNotifyDestNetPort
tptPolicyNotifyDestNetPort.description: The network port (if applicable) of the destination of the packet(s) triggering the policy action.

tptPolicyNotifyStartTimeSec.name: tptPolicyNotifyStartTimeSec
tptPolicyNotifyStartTimeSec.description: The time of the first policy hit, marking the start of the aggregation period for this notification (in seconds since January 1, 1970).

tptPolicyNotifyAlertAction.name: tptPolicyNotifyAlertAction
tptPolicyNotifyAlertAction.description: The action associated with this notification: whether the affected packets were actually blocked, allowed through, or rate-limited.

tptPolicyNotifyConfigAction.name: tptPolicyNotifyConfigAction
tptPolicyNotifyConfigAction.description: The action configured for the policy, which in some cases may differ from the action associated with this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyComponentID.name: tptPolicyNotifyComponentID
tptPolicyNotifyComponentID.description: The component identifier of the policy causing this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyHitCount.name: tptPolicyNotifyHitCount
tptPolicyNotifyHitCount.description: The number of policy hits occurring during the aggregation period for this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyAggregationPeriod.name: tptPolicyNotifyAggregationPeriod
tptPolicyNotifyAggregationPeriod.description: The duration (in minutes) of the aggregation period for this notification.

tptPolicyNotifySeverity.name: tptPolicyNotifySeverity
tptPolicyNotifySeverity.description: The severity of the attack for this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyProtocol.name: tptPolicyNotifyProtocol
tptPolicyNotifyProtocol.description: The network protocol of the packet(s) triggering the policy action.

tptPolicyNotifyAlertTimeSec.name: tptPolicyNotifyAlertTimeSec
tptPolicyNotifyAlertTimeSec.description: The time this alert was initiated, marking the end of the aggregation period for this notification (in seconds since January 1, 1970).

tptPolicyNotifyPacketTrace.name: tptPolicyNotifyPacketTrace
tptPolicyNotifyPacketTrace.description: The value 1 if a corresponding packet trace was logged; 0 if not.

tptPolicyNotifySequence.name: tptPolicyNotifySequence
tptPolicyNotifySequence.description: The log file entry sequence number corresponding to this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyTraceBucket.name: tptPolicyNotifyTraceBucket
tptPolicyNotifyTraceBucket.description: The bucket identifier for a packet trace.

tptPolicyNotifyTraceBegin.name: tptPolicyNotifyTraceBegin
tptPolicyNotifyTraceBegin.description: The starting sequence number for a packet trace.

tptPolicyNotifyTraceEnd.name: tptPolicyNotifyTraceEnd
tptPolicyNotifyTraceEnd.description: The ending sequence number for a packet trace.

tptPolicyNotifyMessageParams.name: tptPolicyNotifyMessageParams
tptPolicyNotifyMessageParams.description: A string containing parameters (separated by vertical bars) matching the Message in the Digital Vaccine (the XML tag is Message).

tptPolicyNotifyAlertType.name: tptPolicyNotifyAlertType
tptPolicyNotifyAlertType.description: A bit field defined as follows: 0x0001 = Alert 0x0002 = Block 0x0020 = Peer-to-peer 0x0040 = Invalid 0x0080 = Threshold 0x0100 = Management.

tptPolicyNotifyInputMphy.name: tptPolicyNotifyInputMphy
tptPolicyNotifyInputMphy.description: The physical input port of the triggering packet(s).

tptPolicyNotifyVlanTag.name: tptPolicyNotifyVlanTag
tptPolicyNotifyVlanTag.description: The VLAN tag of the triggering packet(s).

tptPolicyNotifyZonePair.name: tptPolicyNotifyZonePair
tptPolicyNotifyZonePair.description: A string of the format <in zone UUID>:<out zone UUID> that identifies the zone pair pertaining to this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyActionSetID.name: tptPolicyNotifyActionSetID
tptPolicyNotifyActionSetID.description: The action set uuid associated with this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyRate.name: tptPolicyNotifyRate
tptPolicyNotifyRate.description: The rate-limit, in kbps, of the action set associated with this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyFlowControl.name: tptPolicyNotifyFlowControl
tptPolicyNotifyFlowControl.description: The action set flow control associated with this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyActionSetName.name: tptPolicyNotifyActionSetName
tptPolicyNotifyActionSetName.description: The action set name associated with this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyClientip.name: tptPolicyNotifyClientip
tptPolicyNotifyClientip.description: The client-ip associated with this notification.

tptPolicyNotifyMetadata.name: tptPolicyNotifyMetadata
tptPolicyNotifyMetadata.description: The metadata associated with this notification.

tptPolicyNotifySslInspected.name: tptPolicyNotifySslInspected
tptPolicyNotifySslInspected.description: A flag indicting if the notification is associated with an inspected SSL data stream. This flag is only present on IPS and Quarantine events and doesn't apply to Reputation.

tptPolicyNotifyVirtualSegment.name: tptPolicyNotifyVirtualSegment
tptPolicyNotifyVirtualSegment.description: Virtual segment associated with this notification.

tptPolicyNotify.name: tptPolicyNotify
tptPolicyNotify.description: Notification: Used to inform the management station of a policy alert action (either deny or allow) resulting from a signature match.

SslInspEventType.name: SslInspEventType
SslInspEventType.description: The type of SSL connection, either inbound or outbound.

SslInspAction.name: SslInspAction
SslInspAction.description: The action taken on an SSL connection.

tptPolicyNotifySslInspDetails.name: tptPolicyNotifySslInspDetails
tptPolicyNotifySslInspDetails.description: Free-form field that provides additional details for the action taken on a SSL connection.

tptPolicyNotifySslInspCert.name: tptPolicyNotifySslInspCert
tptPolicyNotifySslInspCert.description: The certificate used to decrypt SSL traffic.

tptPolicyNotifySslInspCltIF.name: tptPolicyNotifySslInspCltIF
tptPolicyNotifySslInspCltIF.description: The client-side interface receiving SSL traffic.

tptPolicyNotifySslInspSrvIF.name: tptPolicyNotifySslInspSrvIF
tptPolicyNotifySslInspSrvIF.description: The server-side interface sending SSL traffic.

tptPolicySslInspNotify.name: tptPolicySslInspNotify
tptPolicySslInspNotify.description: A notification sent when an action is taken on a SSL connection.

tptPolicyLogNotifyDeviceID.name: tptPolicyLogNotifyDeviceID
tptPolicyLogNotifyDeviceID.description: The unique identifier of the device sending this notification.

tptPolicyLogNotifyComponentID.name: tptPolicyLogNotifyComponentID
tptPolicyLogNotifyComponentID.description: The type of log (alert, block, or peer) pertaining to this notification.

tptPolicyLogNotifyNumber.name: tptPolicyLogNotifyNumber
tptPolicyLogNotifyNumber.description: The number of policy log entries since the last SMS log file retrieval.

tptPolicyLogNotifyTrigger.name: tptPolicyLogNotifyTrigger
tptPolicyLogNotifyTrigger.description: The number of policy log entries needed to trigger this notification.

tptPolicyLogNotifySequence.name: tptPolicyLogNotifySequence
tptPolicyLogNotifySequence.description: The current log file entry sequence number.

tptPolicyLogNotify.name: tptPolicyLogNotify
tptPolicyLogNotify.description: Notification: Used to inform the management station that some number of policy log entries of a particular type (alert, block, or peer) occurred since the last time the management station retrieved the corresponding log file.
